---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/trade-in-public-hero.png';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Trade in Public"
	description="A public build log for an automated trading system built with software engineering discipline."
	pubDate={new Date('June 24 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Trade in Public is my public engineering journal for building an automated trading system from
		first principles: requirements, broker/API research, Python implementation, validation, safety
		gates, deployment, and reviews.
	</p>

	<p>
		The project is intentionally framed as a software and learning project. Posts will focus on
		design choices, tradeoffs, verification, and operational lessons rather than signals or market
		persuasion.
	</p>

	<p>
		Nothing here is financial advice, a recommendation, or a signal service. I may hold or change
		positions at any time, and public trade/performance notes will include context and caveats.
	</p>
</Layout>
